<span id="freeTextContainer10808705780821925170">The most boring and most interesting thing I&apos;ve ever read. The most profound and most ridiculous thing I&apos;ve ever read. The most frustrating and most coherent thing I&apos;ve ever read. The most far-seeing and most fantasy-derived thing I&apos;ve ever read. But I&apos;m really glad I read it, occasionally re-read it, and am influenced by it, good or bad.<br/><br/>In my opinion, much of the <i>Communist Manifesto</i> is a restatement of Luke 6:31. No matter if you think this is important or tripe, if you&apos;ve actually read it, the</span>
  <span id="freeText10808705780821925170" style="display:none">The most boring and most interesting thing I've ever read. The most profound and most ridiculous thing I've ever read. The most frustrating and most coherent thing I've ever read. The most far-seeing and most fantasy-derived thing I've ever read. But I'm really glad I read it, occasionally re-read it, and am influenced by it, good or bad.<br /><br />In my opinion, much of the <i>Communist Manifesto</i> is a restatement of Luke 6:31. No matter if you think this is important or tripe, if you've actually read it, then I hope you will agree with me that the intent was a just world. You may disagree about the means, but not its aspiration. Honestly.</span>
