<div id="review_3664447774" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3664447774" />
    <a title="Kevin Kelsey" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/10445368-kevin-kelsey"><img alt="Kevin Kelsey" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1610720844p2/10445368.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3664447774?book_show_action=true">Dec 22, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kevin Kelsey" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kevin Kelsey" href="/user/show/10445368-kevin-kelsey">Kevin Kelsey</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780717802418" href="/book/show/30488.The_Communist_Manifesto">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/10445368-kevin-kelsey?shelf=read-2020">read-2020</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3664447774" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer774865597930128741">Deeply entrenched in the economics of the mid 19th century and full of straw man arguments. It barely even touches on the social reasons that inevitably lead to wealth inequality and the creation of the Proletariat/Bourgeoisie dynamic. It&apos;s much more interested in reform through brute force, which just seems shortsighted with the breadth of historical examples we have to draw on now. All that has done in the past is to create a power vacuum that is immediately filled by a dictator or some other </span>
  <span id="freeText774865597930128741" style="display:none">Deeply entrenched in the economics of the mid 19th century and full of straw man arguments. It barely even touches on the social reasons that inevitably lead to wealth inequality and the creation of the Proletariat/Bourgeoisie dynamic. It's much more interested in reform through brute force, which just seems shortsighted with the breadth of historical examples we have to draw on now. All that has done in the past is to create a power vacuum that is immediately filled by a dictator or some other bad actor. While the goals laid out in this manifesto seem noble ones, I was hoping for more nuance in its approach and found the whole thing underwhelming and somewhat disappointing in a modern context.</span>
  <a data-text-id="774865597930128741" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


